    {
      "id": 358439,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Which of the following dienes have an <i>s</i>-cis conformation, and which have an <i>s</i>-trans conformation? Of the <i>s</i>-trans dienes, which can readily rotate to <i>s</i>-cis?</p>\n<p><b>(a)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc29VIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--b5d51d698235a3bc04495b9da57675326517d347/OChem_14_05_015a.jpg\" alt=\"A cyclohexadiene ring with double bonds between C 1-C 2 and C 3-C 4 fused to a cyclohexane ring.\">\n <b>(b)</b><img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc3NVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--d2497cfc427a2bdd0ebb509091582491fceab9b5/OChem_14_05_015b.jpg\" alt=\"A cyclohexene ring with the double bond at bottom right is fused to another cyclohexene with the double bond at top left.\">\n <b>(c)</b> <img src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBc3dVIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--da757bd7cc2f4cacb58ec7c8bf126e255406697b/OChem_14_05_015c.jpg\" alt=\"In a 5-carbon chain, C 1 is double bonded to C 2. C 3 is double bonded to C 4, which itself is single bonded to a methyl group.\"></p>\n",
      "answers": [],
      "hints": [],
      "formats": [
        "free-response"
      ],
      "combo_choices": [],
      "collaborator_solutions": [
        {
          "images": [],
          "solution_type": "detailed",
          "content_html": "Compound <b>(a)</b> is <i>s</i>-cis. Compound <b>(c)</b> can rotate to <i>s</i>-cis."
        }
      ],
